The paper deals with the problem of identity testing for two special cases of Read-once Oblivious Arithmetic Branching Programs (ROABP). This problem is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) as it involves finding efficient algorithms for a specific computational task. The paper also uses concepts from algebraic geometry and linear algebra, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and scientific computing (cs.SC). The paper's title explicitly mentions identity testing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves constructing hitting-sets, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
